## 22Apr26 ‚Äî v0.4.7 `HOWTO-graph-toolbar-button.md` compliance (still invisible / wrong host)

- **Root cause:** Scored ‚Äúbest‚Äù `.graph-controls` and plugin-global `syncGraphLassoUi` did not match the HOWTO‚Äôs proven checklist: **contentEl-first host**, per-leaf **`Component` + `addChild`**, **`ExtraButtonComponent`**, **`getLeavesOfType`**, **`resize` + `onLayoutReady`**, staggered retries.
- **Actions:** `findGraphControlsHost()` replaces heuristic host. **`GraphLassoLeafToolbar`** uses HOWTO inject + host observer; **`main.ts`** owns `Map` + `scheduleGraphToolbarSync` / `syncAllGraphToolbars` + `getGraphToolbarHost()`. **`selectionController.syncGraphChrome()`** calls `syncAllGraphToolbars()` only.
- **Lessons:** Treat `HOWTO-graph-toolbar-button.md` as the source of truth for graph toolbar injection; duplicate `.graph-controls` nodes make ‚Äúsmart‚Äù host picking a liability.

## 22Apr26 ‚Äî v0.4.8 overlay must not cover `.graph-controls` (toggle stuck on)

- **Symptom:** Toolbar button turned the tool **on** but a second click did not turn it **off** (UI looked stuck active).
- **Root cause:** Lasso overlay used **`position:absolute; inset:0`** on `interactiveEl.parentElement`. That parent can span the **entire graph leaf** (canvas **and** the vertical control strip). The full-size transparent overlay then sat **above** the lasso toggle and ate pointer events.
- **Actions:** `syncOverlayFrame(view)` aligns overlay **top/left/width/height** to `interactiveEl.getBoundingClientRect()` relative to the parent (+ scroll). `ResizeObserver` also observes `interactiveEl`. Toolbar `onClick` resolves host via `this.getToolbarHost()` each click.
- **Lessons:** Graph ‚Äúcanvas parent‚Äù ‚âÝ ‚Äúcanvas box‚Äù; hit-testing overlay must match **interactiveEl** geometry, not the wrapper‚Äôs full box.

## 22Apr26 ‚Äî v0.4.9 hard isolation: mount overlay on `interactiveEl`

- **Symptom:** Crosshair persisted while hovering graph toolbar controls; toggle still sometimes could not switch off.
- **Root cause:** Even with frame math, mounting to `interactiveEl.parentElement` left room for stack/geometry drift where overlay hit-area overlapped control chrome.
- **Actions:** `tryAttach()` now mounts overlay directly to `view.renderer.interactiveEl` (positioned relative if needed). Removed parent-relative offset math in `syncOverlayFrame()` and set local frame `left/top=0` with `interactiveEl.clientWidth/Height`.
- **Lessons:** For graph selection overlays, the safest layer boundary is the exact interaction surface (`interactiveEl`) rather than any wrapper element.

