## 22Apr26 ‚Äî repair: `requestToggleViaCommand` missing from `getGraphToolbarHost()`

- **Trigger:** User report ‚Äî graph lasso toolbar / activation buttons no longer toggled the tool; commands felt disconnected.
- **Root cause:** `GraphToolbarHost` in `graphToolbar.ts` requires **`requestToggleViaCommand`**, and the pin‚Äôs `.onClick` calls it. **`getGraphToolbarHost()` in `main.ts` never supplied that property**, so `tsc` failed with TS2741 and at runtime the click handler invoked **`undefined`** (silent failure or throw depending on bundler/minifier).
- **Actions:** Implemented `requestToggleViaCommand` on the host object: prefer **`(app as AppCommands).commands.executeCommandById(\`${manifest.id}:toggle-graph-select-tool\`)`** so palette logging matches; **fallback** to `toggleToolAndSyncChrome()` if `executeCommandById` returns false. Added **`AppCommands`** helper type (runtime API; Obsidian typings omit `commands` in this repo‚Äôs `obsidian` version).
- **Verify:** `npm run build` clean; in Obsidian, graph pin + **Toggle graph select tool** command both toggle; optional `tail -f` on plugin `debug.log` should show `command.toggle-graph-select-tool` when using the pin.
- **Obsidian CLI (reload after copy):** `obsidian vault="Obsidian Vault 2026" command id=hot-reload:scan-for-changes` or `command id=app:reload` (Obsidian must be running with CLI enabled).

