## 22Apr26 ‚Äî confirmed root cause: overlay mounted on canvas

- **Evidence:** NDJSON `H7/H8` shows `interactiveEl` is **`tagName: "CANVAS"`**, `clientWidth: 1699`, `clientHeight: 826`, but after attach the overlay still reports **`overlayRectWidth: 0`**, **`overlayRectHeight: 0`** despite style widths being set. That means the overlay exists in code but has no rendered box.
- **Root cause:** We were appending the lasso overlay **as a child of the canvas itself**. A canvas is the drawing surface, not a normal layout container for visible HTML children, so the overlay never produced an on-screen reticle.
- **Fix:** Mount the overlay on the canvas‚Äôs **parent element**, keep sizing based on `interactiveEl`, and frame the overlay to the canvas‚Äôs visible box using parent-relative offsets. Instrumentation remains for verification.

## 22Apr26 ‚Äî verification follow-up: overlay blocked graph controls

- **Evidence:** After the mount fix, NDJSON showed `H8` success (`overlayRectWidth: 1699`, `overlayRectHeight: 826`) and `H9` pointerdown events on the overlay, but there was **no second `graphToolbar.ts:pin-onClick`** when the user tried to toggle off from the graph strip. The same session only showed an off-toggle via **ribbon**.
- **Root cause:** The restored full-size overlay now sat above the graph controls in hit-testing order, so a toolbar click landed on the overlay instead of the pin.
- **Fix:** In `selectionController.ts`, when the overlay receives `pointerdown`, inspect `document.elementsFromPoint(...)`; if a real `.graph-controls-button` sits underneath, forward the click to that button and **do not** start a lasso gesture. Added `H10` instrumentation to prove this path during verification.

